WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:01.870
In Service Operations Workspace,

1
00:00:02.269 --> 00:00:05.389
applied filters are managed through the Filter Panel.

2
00:00:05.889 --> 00:00:09.470
Open the Filter Panel to see exactly how the list is being filtered.

3
00:00:09.729 --> 00:00:11.359
To change your filter conditions,

4
00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:13.850
click Advanced View at the bottom of the panel.

5
00:00:14.850 --> 00:00:15.369
From here,

6
00:00:15.489 --> 00:00:18.510
you can modify existing conditions or add new ones using AND

7
00:00:18.510 --> 00:00:21.590
and OR operators to get the view of records you need.

8
00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:25.590
Once you've made your changes,

9
00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:28.780
click Update to apply the new filter conditions.

10
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.860
These changes apply only to your current view of the list.

11
00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:33.299
If you want to keep this view,

12
00:00:33.479 --> 00:00:35.439
you can save it as a personal list.

13
00:00:35.639 --> 00:00:36.220
Otherwise,

14
00:00:36.639 --> 00:00:41.080
the default list view can be restored at any time by reopening the Filter Panel,

15
00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:43.419
then clicking Restore Defaults.
